http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/DarthWiki/Narm?from=Main.Narm

It's when something written is either so overly dramatic or poorly executed that it does not leave the intended effect but instead ends up either humorous or simply disappointing. Admittedly it's pretty subjective, but I saw it that way.

The tone problems are easier to identify. A lot of times it really does sound like you're phrasing it specifically to make it more melodramatic:



Since that time, on the 13th of every month, SCP-1000 has returned, ranging wider then previously.
附加记录：    

This could easily be re-phrased into something more clinical, such as:



Following the incident SCP-1000 has returned every 13th day of a month, and has become more aggressive.
附加记录：    







